.TH MU2EDAQ_NOTIFY 3 "July 2026" "mu2edaq-notify 0.1.0" "Mu2e DAQ"
.SH NAME
mu2edaq_notify \- Python publisher library for the Mu2e DAQ notification
server
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
from mu2edaq_notify import NotifyPublisher, publish_event

pub = NotifyPublisher(server_url=None, token=None, source=None,
                      host=None, timeout=5.0, discover=True)
pub.publish(severity, title, message="", source=None, meta=None)
pub.debug(title, ...)  pub.info(...)  pub.warning(...)
pub.error(...)         pub.critical(...)

publish_event(severity, title, message="", **kwargs)
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
Standard-library-only client for publishing events. The server address
resolves in order: constructor argument, $MU2EDAQ_NOTIFY_URL, then a
mu2edaq-discovery multicast query (filter app=notify) when
\fBdiscover\fR is true. The bearer token comes from the constructor or
$MU2EDAQ_NOTIFY_TOKEN.
.PP
\fBpublish()\fR returns True when the server accepted the event and
False otherwise. It never raises on delivery failure: publishing a
notification must not be able to take down a DAQ application.
.SH EVENT FIELDS
severity (debug|info|warning|error|critical), title (<=200 chars),
message (<=4000 chars), source, host (defaults to the local hostname),
meta (string map).
.SH EXAMPLE
.nf
from mu2edaq_notify import NotifyPublisher
pub = NotifyPublisher(token="api-token", source="dtc-monitor")
pub.error("DTC link down", "ROC link 3 lost lock",
          meta={"run": "107001"})
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
mu2edaq-notify(1), mu2edaq_notify_cpp(3)
